name: I have been sick for awhile now
description: I have been sick for a while now. I have walked through dust and I have seen the pits. I have seen the cinders and the black cinders. But thirties, forties, I was in the know: the air is full of powder ever since the rising. How can you have a conscience when you have lost it all? I've been oppressed by the papacy, I've been oppressed by the vicar, I've been oppressed by the curia. But I have seen the light, I have seen the way, I have seen the end. And it's the same now: the end will come again like the plague, and then only the end will come again when I reach the ragged shore.
